sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router/Istio Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant NotebookSvc as Notebook Service (ClusterIP)<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant NotebookPod as Notebook Pod (StatefulSet)<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant DSP as Data Science Pipeline API<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant Tekton as Tekton Pipeline Controller<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Quay as Quay.io Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant RuntimePod as Runtime Image Pod<br/>Tekton PipelineRun

    Note over User,RuntimePod: Flow 1: User Accesses Jupyter Notebook

    User->>Router: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+<br/>OAuth Bearer Token
    Router->>OAuth: HTTP/8888<br/>Bearer Token validation
    OAuth->>NotebookSvc: HTTP/8888<br/>mTLS (if Service Mesh)<br/>Session Cookie
    NotebookSvc->>NotebookPod: HTTP/8888<br/>Jupyter Token/Cookie
    NotebookPod-->>NotebookSvc: JupyterLab UI Response
    NotebookSvc-->>OAuth: HTML Response
    OAuth-->>Router: HTML Response
    Router-->>User: HTTPS Response

    Note over NotebookPod,S3: Flow 2: Notebook Accesses S3 Storage

    NotebookPod->>S3: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+<br/>AWS Signature v4<br/>(from mounted secret)
    S3-->>NotebookPod: Model Data / Datasets

    Note over NotebookPod,RuntimePod: Flow 3: Elyra Submits Pipeline to Data Science Pipelines

    NotebookPod->>DSP: HTTP/8888<br/>mTLS (if Service Mesh)<br/>Bearer Token (ServiceAccount)
    DSP->>Tekton: HTTP/8080<br/>mTLS (if Service Mesh)<br/>ServiceAccount Token<br/>Create PipelineRun
    Tekton->>Quay: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+<br/>Pull Secret<br/>Pull Runtime Image
    Quay-->>Tekton: Runtime Image
    Tekton->>RuntimePod: Create Pod from Runtime Image
    RuntimePod->>S3: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+<br/>AWS Signature v4<br/>Load Input Data
    S3-->>RuntimePod: Input Data
    Note over RuntimePod: Execute Pipeline Step<br/>(Python Code)
    RuntimePod->>S3: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+<br/>AWS Signature v4<br/>Save Output
    S3-->>RuntimePod: Confirmation
    RuntimePod-->>Tekton: Step Complete
    Tekton-->>DSP: PipelineRun Status
    DSP-->>NotebookPod: Pipeline Execution Results

    Note over Quay,NotebookPod: Flow 4: Image Build and Distribution

    rect rgb(240, 240, 240)
        Note over Quay: Build System (Konflux)<br/>pushes images
        Quay->>Quay: Store Image<br/>HTTPS/443<br/>Robot Account Token
    end

    rect rgb(240, 240, 240)
        Note over NotebookPod: ImageStream Import
        NotebookPod->>Quay: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+<br/>Pull Secret<br/>Import Image
        Quay-->>NotebookPod: Image Layers
    end

    rect rgb(240, 240, 240)
        Note over NotebookPod: Kubelet pulls image
        NotebookPod->>Quay: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+<br/>Pull Secret<br/>Pull for Pod Creation
        Quay-->>NotebookPod: Container Image
    end
